commit.message:
filter repositories in search results

Add a command line option to filter search results based on the name
of the repository. The hound API supports passing a list of
repositories and filtering server-side, but not based on a pattern.

commit.message:
Fix issues

- wrong openstack generated url
- flake8 warnings
- ignore flake8 W504

These fix will make the pep8's CI job happy.

Also adding the tox `venv` target to run beagle commands on virtualenv
managed by tox

Refactor pipelines

Refactor travis config and tox to base all tests on tox.

- Unit tests doesn't exist so we ignore them.
- Coverage have now a dedicated tox target.
- Drop the underlaying shell script
- Remove pep8 from the default tox envlist to avoid automatical run
  (could by surrounded locally in a second time by adding git hooks)

Normally these changes should fix the travis CI issue related to unit
tests not found.
